    "Background": {
      "text": "Inflammation of large airways of the lung\nPneumonia\nmust be excluded by clinical evaluation or by CXR\nIf all 5 are negative pneumonia is safely excluded:\nHR >100\nRR >24\nTemperature >38 (100.4)\nExam findings consistent with focal consolidation, egophony, or fremitus\nAge >64yr",
      "subsections": {
        "Epidemiology": {
          "text": "Viruses are most common cause\nInfluenza\n, paraflu,\nRSV\n,\ncoronavirus\n,\nadenovirus\n,\nrhinovirus\nBacterial cause occurs in <10% of cases\nMycoplasma\n,\nC. pneumoniae\n,\npertussis\n(1% of bronchitis cases)",
          "tables": []
